UN Says Nigeria Ogoni Oil Pollution Clean-Up Needs $1 Billion in 5 Years

-- B y   D u l u e   M b a c h u
-- 
2011-08-04T16:04:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/un-says-nigeria-ogoni-oil-pollution-clean-up-needs-1-billion-in-5-years.html
Oil pollution in  Nigeria ’s Ogoni
district is worse than previously thought and could “prove to
be the world’s most wide-ranging and long term oil clean-up
exercise ever undertaken,” costing more than $1 billion in five
years, the United Nations Environment Programme said in a report
released today in abuja, the capital.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  